<p>President Trump told reporters aboard Air Force One that the United States is not planning military strikes inside Venezuela, responding &quot;No, it’s not true&quot; to reports suggesting imminent operations . His denial comes as Washington has deployed an unusually large naval force to the Caribbean and carried out maritime strikes on vessels it says were involved in drug trafficking . Media reports and U.S. outlets have said the administration has discussed potential targets on Venezuelan soil, including military facilities, while officials have also authorized covert operations inside Venezuela — developments that have prompted questions from regional leaders and U.S. senators seeking details on the strategy and legal basis .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/8XWg1oOujs8hu8IqaSQLVWrw7Q4ozn37e3YNeL9P0UJRBkuuqXZ8fWk9athJ1CoFkgqITABJTTtxvDCecZO8u7-SuWV514V6gwIPp4xdRVve3M5tlnYA0VZwdFlW_8miYn8d6bKWnt2aa1s8GVwNBFwue67ziEqdSEjayYxZxTmTLXSs0wxmRf-SuZyPIVtjHvko8vPwYdyHGO0KCgsrbR7_tlI' alt='President Trump speaking to reporters aboard Air Force One after denying plans for strikes on Venezuela' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Covert operations: Reporting says the administration authorized covert CIA operations inside Venezuela as part of its anti-drug effort, a step that expands activity beyond maritime strikes .</li><li>Reported targets: U.S. media cited by other outlets have identified possible targets inside Venezuela, including military facilities allegedly used to smuggle drugs, though officials have denied imminent land strikes .</li><li>Maritime toll: Coverage links U.S. maritime strikes to the destruction of multiple suspected smuggling boats since September, with reporting describing the operations as deadly and prompting regional concern .</li><li>Congressional scrutiny: Several U.S. senators have publicly asked the administration for briefings and clearer explanations of the anti-drug strategy and its legal authority, signaling domestic oversight pressure .</li></ul><blockquote>No, it’s not true. - President Trump</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>President Trump / White House: The president denied that he was planning strikes inside Venezuela, answering &quot;No, it’s not true&quot; when asked about reports of imminent operations . (<a href='https://english.elpais.com/usa/2025-10-31/trump-says-he-is-not-considering-military-strike-against-venezuela.html'>El País</a>)</li><li>Venezuelan government (Nicolás Maduro): Maduro rejected U.S. allegations of drug trafficking support, vowed to defend the country, and accused the U.S. of fabricating a new war . (<a href='https://www.rt.com/news/627216-trump-denies-strikes-venezuela/'>RT</a>)</li><li>Colombian president (Gustavo Petro): President Petro condemned Washington&#x27;s actions and said one of the strikes had killed an ordinary fisherman, criticizing the operation&#x27;s toll on civilians . (<a href='https://www.rt.com/news/627216-trump-denies-strikes-venezuela/'>RT</a>)</li><li>U.S. senators: Senators have demanded answers on the anti-drug strategy, seeking details about objectives, oversight and legal authority for expanded operations . (<a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/us-senators-want-answers-on-anti-drug-strategy-as-venezuela-tensions-rise/article70228488.ece'>The Hindu</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/11/1/trump-says-not-planning-us-strikes-on-venezuela'>Trump says not planning US strikes on Venezuela</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.rt.com/news/627216-trump-denies-strikes-venezuela/'>Trump denies planning strikes in Venezuela</a> - rt.com</li><li><a href='https://english.elpais.com/usa/2025-10-31/trump-says-he-is-not-considering-military-strike-against-venezuela.html'>Trump says he is not considering military strike against Venezuela</a> - elpais.com</li><li><a href='https://www.pbs.org/newshour/politics/watch-trump-denies-u-s-is-considering-strikes-against-vene